race.comment: CUT NO ICE (4) resumes here much improved and then came back and found one better over this trip. Fitter again and maps well. Keeps the handy 2kg claim and can go one better. CARING LASS (3) was well beaten in third but improved having her second start since the switch from a Sydney stable. She can race forward from the inside barrier and she can fight out the finish if near best. ASTRODEAN (7) resumed in good order but has been plainer the two since. Might be looking for this trip and he's up to this if on-song. The tongue tie going on for the first time is a key gear addition. LUCAS THE YOUNGER (1) just missed over 1400m at Murray Bridge at big odds making further improvement. A niggle at this distance but on that effort deserves consideration.
